Given a trapezoid $ABCD$ where $\overline{AB}$ is parallel to $\overline{CD}$. The lengths of the parallel sides are $AB = 7$ units and $CD = 10$ units. A segment $EF$ is drawn parallel to $\overline{AB}$ with $E$ lying on $\overline{AD}$ and $F$ lying on $\overline{BC}$. The ratio of $BF:FC$ is $3:4$. The problem is to find the length of $EF$, expressed as a common fraction. egin{center} egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) -- (7,0) -- (8,-4) -- (-2,-4) -- cycle;\draw (3/7*-2+4/7*0,-4) -- (3/7*8+4/7*7,0);
ode at (0,0.2) {$A$};
ode at (7,0.2) {$B$};
ode at (8,-4.2) {$C$};
ode at (-2,-4.2) {$D$};
ode at (3/7*-2+4/7*0,-4.2) {$E$};
ode at (3/7*8+4/7*7,0.2) {$F$};\end{tikzpicture}\end{center}
